<tr>
  <td class="diff-marker">−</td>
  <td class="diff-deletedline"><div>Improving this article could be done by presenting the history of the Act more systematically<del class="diffchange diffchange-inline">. Right now, the article jumps from 18th century to 21st century in many sections which makes it hard to get a sense of the actual evolution of the Act in time</del>. Also, reading about the Act without discussing (just a little) the colossal ramifications they had on aboriginals and the relationship between the Canadian government and aboriginal tribes really makes this article tone deaf to the subject matter being dealt with. [[Special:Contributions/131.137.245.209|131.137.245.209]] ([[User talk:131.137.245.209|talk]]) 17:36, 3 February 2015 (UTC)</div></td>
  <td class="diff-marker">+</td>
  <td class="diff-addedline"><div>Improving this article could be done by presenting the history of the Act more systematically. Also, reading about the Act without discussing (just a little) the colossal ramifications they had on aboriginals and the relationship between the Canadian government and aboriginal tribes really makes this article tone deaf to the subject matter being dealt with.<ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline"> Yes, its nice to have main articles for further reading but other than stating that the goal was to assimilate the Indians, the article does not present any indication of success or failure despite 300 years of application. </ins> [[Special:Contributions/131.137.245.209|131.137.245.209]] ([[User talk:131.137.245.209|talk]]) 17:36, 3 February 2015 (UTC)</div></td>
</tr>
