<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Improving_Article">Improving Article</span></h2>
<p>What are some ways we could improve the article? <a href="/wiki/User:OldManRivers" title="User:OldManRivers">OldManRivers</a> 18:42, 15 March 2007 (UTC)</p>
<dl>
<dd>(1) Needs many more footnotes. <s>(2) Section 88 section needs updating to include info on <a href="/w/index.php?title=Dick_v._The_Queen&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Dick v. The Queen (page does not exist)">Dick v. The Queen</a>, which revolutionized the meaning of that section.</s> (3) Needs information on the movements to amend (or abolish) the Indian Act and the motives for such movements. <a href="/wiki/User:CanadianCaesar" title="User:CanadianCaesar">CanadianCaesar</a> <small><a href="/wiki/User_talk:CanadianCaesar" title="User talk:CanadianCaesar">Et tu, Brute?</a></small> 18:53, 15 March 2007 (UTC)
<dl>
<dd>There was also that stuff about the Governance Act that the Liberals put forward in the Early 1990's. I was really young at the time, but I remember the AFN gathering Vancouver. They voted on it and all the bands from BC voted against it. (And no wonder. What province has barely any treaties?) I've actually never heard of <a href="/w/index.php?title=Dick_v._The_Queen&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Dick v. The Queen (page does not exist)">Dick v. The Queen</a>. And I'll see what I can do about movement to abolish the Indian Act. <a href="/wiki/User:OldManRivers" title="User:OldManRivers">OldManRivers</a> 20:04, 15 March 2007 (UTC)
<dl>
<dd>I handled the Dick v. The Queen material. <a href="/wiki/User:CanadianCaesar" title="User:CanadianCaesar">CanadianCaesar</a> <small><a href="/wiki/User_talk:CanadianCaesar" title="User talk:CanadianCaesar">Et tu, Brute?</a></small> 22:37, 16 March 2007 (UTC)</dd>
</dl>
